<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Use the same key for different seeds if they are the same type and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// reference the same pointer, even if at different offsets. This directs</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00179" /><CodeLine lineNumber="179"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Trying to vectorize too many seeds at once is expensive in</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="182"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// size-limited by sbvec-seed-bundle-size-limit.  TODO: There might be a</span></CodeLine>
